          <p><strong>Does the unblocked version have all levels?</strong> Yes. The game here is the full HTML5 browser version of Stickman Hook — the same 100+ levels, the same physics engine, the same skins system. Nothing is cut, reduced, or different from the standard browser version of the game.</p>
          <p><strong>Will the game remember my progress at school?</strong> Progress is stored in your browser's local storage. This means progress is tied to the specific browser and device you use. If you play on a school computer today, that progress won't transfer to a home computer automatically. For persistent cross-device progress, the mobile app (free on iOS and Android) uses cloud saves.</p>
          <p><strong>Can I play Stickman Hook on a school iPad?</strong> Yes. Stickman Hook's browser version works on Safari on iOS. Open this page in Safari on the iPad and tap the screen to play. The native iOS app from the App Store also works on iPads.</p>
        </div>
